Class TFF

    ReadableASCII

    @Reference(author={"Janyce Wiebe","Theresa Wilson","Claire Cardie"},
           title="Annotating expressions of opinions and emotions in language. ",
           type=Article,
           year="2005")
public class TFF
extends Object
implements ReadableASCII
    The TFF data format is the word clue format used by OpinionFinder. Details of MPQA and this format can be found: http://www.cs.pitt.edu/mpqa/

    The way to think about TFF entries are clues that a given word (or set of words) give to the sentiment and subjectivity of a given phrase. There are many clever ways to use this information highlighted in this paper:

    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
